023package org.opt4j.benchmarks.zdt;
024
025import org.opt4j.benchmarks.BinaryCopyDecoder;
026import org.opt4j.benchmarks.BinaryCreator;
027import org.opt4j.benchmarks.BinaryToDoubleDecoder;
028import org.opt4j.benchmarks.Bits;
029import org.opt4j.benchmarks.DoubleCopyDecoder;
030import org.opt4j.benchmarks.DoubleCreator;
031import org.opt4j.benchmarks.N;
032import org.opt4j.core.config.annotations.Citation;
033import org.opt4j.core.config.annotations.Citation.PublicationMonth;
034import org.opt4j.core.config.annotations.Info;
035import org.opt4j.core.config.annotations.Order;
036import org.opt4j.core.config.annotations.Required;
037import org.opt4j.core.problem.Creator;
038import org.opt4j.core.problem.Decoder;
039import org.opt4j.core.problem.Evaluator;
040import org.opt4j.core.problem.ProblemModule;
041
042/**
043 * The {@link ZDTModule} configures the ZDT benchmarks, see Zitzler et al. 2000.
044 * 
045 * @author lukasiewycz
046 * 
047 */
048@Info("ZDT Problem Suite.")
049@Citation(title = "Comparison of Multiobjective Evolutionary Algorithms: Empirical Results", authors = "Eckart Zitzler, Kalyanmoy Deb, and Lothar Thiele", journal = "Evolutionary Computation Volume", volume = 8, number = 2, month = PublicationMonth.JUNE, year = 2000)
050public class ZDTModule extends ProblemModule {
051
052        @Order(0)
053        @Info("The ZDT function.")
054        protected Function function = Function.ZDT1;
055
056        @Order(1)
057        @Info("The size of the search space.")
058        protected int n = 30;
059
060        @Order(2)
061        @Required(property = "function", elements = { "ZDT1", "ZDT2", "ZDT3", "ZDT4", "ZDT6" })
062        @Info("The encoding of the optimization problem.")
063        protected Encoding encoding = Encoding.BINARY;
064
065        @Order(3)
066        @Required(property = "encoding", elements = { "BINARY" })
067        @Info("The number of bits per double value.")
068        protected int bits = 30;
069
070        /**
071         * The used ZDT function.
072         * 
073         * @author lukasiewycz
074         */
075        public enum Function {
076                /**
077                 * Use the ZDT1 function.
078                 */
079                ZDT1,
080                /**
081                 * Use the ZDT2 function.
082                 */
083                ZDT2,
084                /**
085                 * Use the ZDT3 function.
086                 */
087                ZDT3,
088                /**
089                 * Use the ZDT4 function.
090                 */
091                ZDT4,
092                /**
093                 * Use the ZDT5 function.
094                 */
095                ZDT5,
096                /**
097                 * Use the ZDT6 function.
098                 */
099                ZDT6;
100        }
101
102        /**
103         * The used encoding type.
104         * 
105         * @author lukasiewycz
106         */
107        public enum Encoding {
108                /**
109                 * Use double values.
110                 */
111                DOUBLE,
112                /**
113                 * Use binary values.
114                 */
115                BINARY;
116        }
117
118        /**
119         * Returns the number of bits per double value.
120         * 
121         * @return the bits
122         */
123        public int getBits() {
124                return bits;
125        }
126
127        /**
128         * Sets the number of bits per double value.
129         * 
130         * @param bits
131         *            the bits to set
132         */
133        public void setBits(int bits) {
134                this.bits = bits;
135        }
136
137        /**
138         * Returns the encoding (double or binary).
139         * 
140         * @return the encoding
141         */
142        public Encoding getEncoding() {
143                return encoding;
144        }
145
146        /**
147         * Set the encoding (double or binary).
148         * 
149         * @param encoding
150         *            the encoding
151         */
152        public void setEncoding(Encoding encoding) {
153                this.encoding = encoding;
154                validate();
155        }
156
157        /**
158         * Returns the ZDT function.
159         * 
160         * @return the ZDT function
161         */
162        public Function getFunction() {
163                return function;
164        }
165
166        /**
167         * Sets the ZDT function.
168         * 
169         * @param function
170         *            the ZDT function
171         */
172        public void setFunction(Function function) {
173                this.function = function;
174                validate();
175
176                switch (function) {
177                case ZDT1:
178                        n = 30;
179                        break;
180                case ZDT2:
181                        n = 30;
182                        break;
183                case ZDT3:
184                        n = 30;
185                        break;
186                case ZDT4:
187                        n = 10;
188                        break;
189                case ZDT5:
190                        n = 11;
191                        break;
192                case ZDT6:
193                        n = 10;
194                        break;
195                default:
196                        n = 30;
197                        break;
198                }
199
200        }
201
202        /**
203         * Returns the n value.
204         * 
205         * @return the n value
206         */
207        public int getN() {
208                return n;
209        }
210
211        /**
212         * Sets the n value.
213         * 
214         * @param n
215         *            the n value
216         */
217        public void setN(int n) {
218                this.n = n;
219        }
220
221        /**
222         * Validates all settings. In particular, ZDT5 can be encoded binary only.
223         */
224        protected void validate() {
225                if (function == Function.ZDT5 && encoding == Encoding.DOUBLE) {
226                        encoding = Encoding.BINARY;
227                }
228        }
229
230        /*
231         * (non-Javadoc)
232         * 
233         * @see org.opt4j.start.Opt4JModule#config()
234         */
235        @Override
236        public void config() {
237                validate();
238
239                Class<? extends Creator<?>> creator = null;
240                Class<? extends Decoder<?, ?>> decoder = null;
241                Class<? extends Evaluator<?>> evaluator = null;
242
243                switch (encoding) {
244                case BINARY:
245                        if (function == Function.ZDT5) {
246                                creator = ZDT5BinaryCreator.class;
247                                decoder = BinaryCopyDecoder.class;
248                        } else {
249                                creator = BinaryCreator.class;
250                                decoder = BinaryToDoubleDecoder.class;
251                        }
252                        break;
253                case DOUBLE:
254                        // only for ZDT1,ZDT2,ZDT3,ZDT4,ZDT6
255                        creator = DoubleCreator.class;
256                        decoder = DoubleCopyDecoder.class;
257                        break;
258                default:
259                        if (function == Function.ZDT5) {
260                                creator = ZDT5BinaryCreator.class;
261                                decoder = BinaryCopyDecoder.class;
262                        } else {
263                                creator = BinaryCreator.class;
264                                decoder = BinaryToDoubleDecoder.class;
265                        }
266                        break;
267                }
268
269                switch (function) {
270                case ZDT1:
271                        evaluator = ZDT1.class;
272                        break;
273                case ZDT2:
274                        evaluator = ZDT2.class;
275                        break;
276                case ZDT3:
277                        evaluator = ZDT3.class;
278                        break;
279                case ZDT4:
280                        evaluator = ZDT4.class;
281                        break;
282                case ZDT5:
283                        evaluator = ZDT5.class;
284                        break;
285                case ZDT6:
286                        evaluator = ZDT6.class;
287                        break;
288                default:
289                }
290
291                bindConstant(N.class).to(n);
292                bindConstant(Bits.class).to(bits);
293                bindProblem(creator, decoder, evaluator);
294
295        }
296
297}
